    type: "technical",
    difficulty: "Medium",
    question: "Explain database replication. Compare primary-replica and multi-master replication. What are the trade-offs?",
    hint: "Cover read scaling, write bottleneck, replication lag, failover, and conflict resolution in multi-master.",
    keyPoints: ["Primary handles writes, replicas serve reads", "Replication lag causes stale reads", "Failover promotes replica to primary", "Multi-master enables write scaling but introduces conflicts", "Semi-synchronous for durability without full sync overhead"],
    modelAnswer: `**Primary-Replica Replication**: All writes go to primary. Replicas asynchronously copy the binary log. 1 primary and 5 replicas give 6x read throughput. Failover: on primary failure, a replica is promoted (automated via Orchestrator or MHA). **Replication Modes**: Asynchronous (MySQL default): Fast writes but replica may lag — stale reads. Semi-synchronous: Primary waits for at least 1 replica to acknowledge. Balances durability and latency. Synchronous: Primary waits for all replicas (PostgreSQL synchronous_commit = on). No data loss but high write latency. **Replication Lag Problem**: After a write, user reading immediately from a replica may see old data. Solutions: (1) Read-your-own-writes: route reads-after-writes to primary for that user session. (2) Monotonic reads: always route a user to the same replica. (3) Causal consistency with version vectors. **Multi-Master Replication**: Multiple nodes accept writes. Replication propagates writes to all masters. Pros: Write scalability, geographic distribution (each region has a local master). Cons: Write conflicts — two masters update the same row simultaneously. Conflict resolution: last-write-wins by timestamp (but clocks drift), per-field merge, application-level resolution. Use when: geographic distribution required for write latency, or write throughput exceeds single-node capacity. Examples: CockroachDB, Galera Cluster, Amazon Aurora Global Database. **Read Replica Capacity**: Primary at 10K WPS. Add 5 read replicas for 50K RPS on reads. Most apps are 80% reads.`,
