    modelAnswer: `Test Cycle — Complete End-to-End Process:

Step 1: Build Receipt
Dev team deploys a new build with release notes (stories included, defects fixed, known issues). Tester confirms build version matches before any testing begins.

Step 2: Smoke Test (Build Verification)
Execute 10-15 critical test cases covering core flows (login, main navigation, one end-to-end workflow).
  Gate: Smoke FAILS → reject build, wait for fix, do not begin full testing.
  Gate: Smoke PASSES → proceed to full test execution.

Step 3: Full Test Execution
Execute all planned test cases in priority order: Critical and High first, then Medium, then Low.
Mark each: Pass / Fail / Blocked / Not Run.
For every FAILED case: immediately log a defect in Jira with steps, expected vs actual, severity, priority, screenshots, and logs.
For BLOCKED: document the blocking reason.

Step 4: Daily Status Report
Share daily with team and stakeholders:
  - Execution: Planned / Executed / Passed / Failed / Blocked counts
  - Defects: Opened today / Total open / Fixed / Closed / Deferred
  - Blockers: environment issues, missing test data, build instability

Step 5: Regression After Each Fix Build
When dev deploys a new build: retest each fixed bug (verify the fix) and run the regression suite (verify nothing else broke). Repeat until Exit Criteria are satisfied.

Exit criteria example:
  - 95%+ of planned test cases executed
  - 100% of Critical/High defects closed
  - Zero Showstopper bugs open
  - UAT sign-off received`,
