    modelAnswer: `Use Case Testing derives test cases directly from use case documentation, ensuring complete coverage of all documented system interactions.

Use Case Structure:
- Actor: who initiates the action (Registered Customer)
- Goal: what the actor wants to achieve (Complete an order)
- Preconditions: system state before the use case begins (User is logged in, cart has items)
- Main Success Scenario (MSS): the step-by-step flow when everything goes correctly
- Extensions: alternative or error flows branching from specific steps
- Postconditions: system state after successful completion (Order created, payment captured, confirmation sent)

Example Use Case: UC-05 Complete Online Order

Actor: Registered Customer
Precondition: Customer is logged in; cart contains at least one in-stock item
Main Success Scenario:
  1. Customer reviews cart contents
  2. Customer enters/selects delivery address
  3. Customer selects delivery method
  4. Customer enters payment details
  5. System validates payment
  6. Order is created and confirmation displayed
Postcondition: Order record created; stock decremented; confirmation email sent

Extensions:
  2a. Customer has no saved address → enters new address
  3a. Selected delivery method has a surcharge → surcharge shown and confirmed
  5a. Payment fails → error shown, customer can retry with different details
  5b. Item out of stock at payment time → customer notified, order not created

Derived Test Cases:

TC-UC05-01 (from MSS): Happy path — existing address, saved payment, successful order
TC-UC05-02 (from 2a): New address entry — all fields validated, address saved to account
TC-UC05-03 (from 3a): Surcharge delivery — correct surcharge shown, total updated before confirmation
TC-UC05-04 (from 5a): Payment failure — clear error, cart and address retained, retry works
TC-UC05-05 (from 5b): Out-of-stock at payment — clear message, no partial order, no charge applied

Coverage check: Every extension in the use case maps to at least one test case. The postconditions are explicitly verified in TC-UC05-01 (email received, stock decremented).`,
